## No-any rule

**Never use `any` in `src/types/`**, `src/lib/acf/`, or `src/components/sections/`.

Use `unknown` for values of unknown shape, then narrow with type guards or field-mapper helpers. The codebase currently has zero `any` in section-critical files — maintain this.

Acceptable patterns:
```ts
// ✅ unknown + field mapper
const title = asString(row.title);

// ✅ unknown + type assertion with narrow cast
const items = row.items as { text?: unknown; icon?: unknown }[];

// ❌ never
const items = row.items as any[];
```

---

## Adding a new section type — type-layer checklist

1. Define `MyNewSectionT = CoreSection & { type: "my_new_section"; ... }` in `sections.ts`.
2. Add any sub-item types above it (e.g. `MyNewSectionItemT`).
3. Add `| MyNewSectionT` to the `AnySectionT` union.
4. The `PAGE_SECTION_ACF_LAYOUTS satisfies Record<AnySectionT["type"], true>` constraint in `normalize-page-sections.ts` will now error until the key is added there too.
5. Both `assertNever` switch statements will error until their cases are added.
